I used jackson in Android app to convert objects to json and json to objects. The app also receives json from a web app which has full field names. Since proguard in android obfuscates all names, I was getting an error only while processing json from web. 
So for the json containing unobfuscated names, getters and setters of model classes are kept. 

Since getters are setters are kept, while converting object to json, jackson was adding both obfuscated and unobfuscated names to json (data duplication) . To prevent that, private fields of model classes are kept. So now only full unobfuscated fields are present in json. 

